data.enText: connected with the land or sea that is owned by a particular country
Both countries feel they have territorial claims to (= have a right to own) the islands.
data.chText: 两个国家都认为对这些岛屿拥有主权。

data.enText: guarding and defending an area of land that they believe to be their own
the instinctive territoriality of some animals
data.chText: 一些动物本能的地盘性

data.enText: The country was trying to expand territorially.
data.chText: 这个国家在设法扩张领土。

tr: nonprofessional soldier member of a territorial military unit
belonging to the territory of any state or ruler
of or relating to a territory
example: the territorial government of the Virgin Islands
territorial claims made by a country

example.ex: It is the only republic which has no territorial disputes with the others...
example.tran: 它是唯一和其他国家没有领土争端的共和国。

example.ex: Both Chile and Argentina feel very strongly about their territorial claims to Antarctica.
example.tran: 智利和阿根廷对于南极的领土主张都持强硬态度。

value.def: Territorial means concerned with the ownership of a particular area of land or water.
In Britain, the Territorials are the members of the Territorial Army .

example.ex: Two cats or more in one house will also exhibit territorial behaviour.
example.tran: 一家若有两只或更多的猫，也会表现出争夺地盘的行为。

value.def: If you describe an animal or its behaviour as territorial, you mean that it has an area which it regards as its own, and which it defends when other animals try to enter it.
value.tran: (动物或其行为)地盘意识强的，占地为王的
